  <prompt>Read task 001's decision doc draft at `notes/decisions/030-dispatch-path.md`. Inspect `sprk_playbookconsumer` entity + service implementation (originated in `work/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1` Phase 1R). Determine whether the daily-briefing widget can be registered as a consumer that dispatches to `DAILY-BRIEFING-NARRATE` with structured payload. Finalize the decision in `notes/decisions/030-dispatch-path.md` with rationale per AC-12c.</prompt>
  <role>SPAARKE platform developer. Follow ADRs strictly. AI dispatch + playbook routing research; survey existing consumer dispatch infrastructure before committing to an implementation path.</role>
  <goal>Decision document `notes/decisions/030-dispatch-path.md` finalized with: (a) selected path (A: consumer registration, or B: direct AnalysisOrchestrationService.RunPlaybookAsync with degenerate playbook), (b) concrete evidence from inspecting consumer service + entity, (c) implementation outline that task 031 will follow, (d) explicit AC-12c rationale.</goal>
  <context>
    <background>R3 UAT defect: /narrate hardcodes the LLM prompt inside the endpoint, which prevents prompt iteration without recompile and was identified as a hallucination contributor. R4 FR-12 requires /narrate to dispatch via the existing playbook engine. Path A (preferred) leverages `sprk_playbookconsumer` registration created in chat-routing-redesign-r1 Phase 1R, mapping the daily-briefing widget as a consumer keyed to playbook code `DAILY-BRIEFING-NARRATE`. Path B falls back to direct invocation of `AnalysisOrchestrationService.RunPlaybookAsync` with a degenerate playbook definition (no Dataverse query node). The dispatch path must be decided before implementation begins in task 031.</background>
